commit.message:
add keyword argv to main, allowing calls like:

import gprof2dot

gprof2dot.main([
        pstfile,
        "--output", dotfile,
        "--format", "pstats",
        "--colormap", "color",
    ])

Sum call counts in JSON format.

This populates the number of times each function is called so that it will show
up in the graph output as in other formats.

Add --nodel-label option to specify the measurements shown on the node label(s).

From the --help:

    --nodel-label=MEASURE measurements to on show the node (can be specified
                          multiple times): self-time, self-time-percentage,
                          total-time or total-time-percentage [default: total-
                          time-percentage, self-time-percentage]

Fixes #3

Don't hardcode theme names in opt parsing code

This change makes them work the same way as formatNames.

Update instructions for installing dependencies on Linux.

Fixes https://github.com/jrfonseca/gprof2dot/issues/49

fix Profile.prune() for cases when filename is not set

also add similar pruning for function.module (if set)

Add README and LICENSE to the manifest.

Fixes https://github.com/jrfonseca/gprof2dot/issues/42

Deprecated: python 2.6

Explicitly defined python 2.7 as only python2 supported version

Add US spelling for option to color nodes by self-time.

While preserving British spelling for backwards compatibility.

Per https://github.com/jrfonseca/gprof2dot/issues/5#issuecomment-284354413

Ignore # comments anywhere on callgrind files.

Just like PerfParser does.

Also add a test case.

Fixes https://github.com/jrfonseca/gprof2dot/issues/35
Skip header '# callgrind format' if any.
@mantognini suggestion to be able to prune from multiple paths

Remove debug module.

Addresses the issue reported in
https://github.com/jrfonseca/gprof2dot/pull/31
